      {
        "id": 4715556,
        "name": "Rich Brown",
        "username": "Rich_Brown",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/rich_brown/{size}/2408_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-31T16:40:25.001Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"JeffK\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"338782\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/73ab20/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> JeffK:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>1975 Sterling Vineyards Cabernet Sauvignon Napa Valley</strong></p>\n<p>Opened by Allred at his 50th birthday dinner. Made by the founding winemaker Ric Forman. 2 bottles were opened and the first was maderized. Decanted for sediment before drinking. This bottle showed very well. Smooth and elegant. Notes of dried mushrooms, wet earth and red berries. Integrated tannins. I liked this better than the 1975 Beau-Sejour Becot which was also opened. 91-92 points.</p>\n<p>VM</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Ahhh, i freaking love this wine!  Bummer one of your bottles was maderized but glad the second on showed better.  These Ric Forman wines from the 70\u2019s are such a gift.  Thanks for posting!</p>\n<p>Here\u2019s my note from a few years ago:</p>\n<p>I was in the mood for some aged-cab goodness and snagged this from the cellar on the fly.  Not gonna  lie, I was a little worried about the wine when I cut the capsule and found the cork to be completely soaked through, but my concerns were erased the minute that I Durand\u2019d (that\u2019s a word, right?) The cork.   Soaring aromatics of red fruits and a beautiful crimson color with literally no bricking.  In the mouth this was seriously just happiness in a glass.  Sweet cassis, cherries, a hint of cedar, and some tannins on the long finish.  Lovely acidity and just perfectly integrated.  Classic old school Napa drinking at its absolute peak right now with no end in sight (crazy it still has tannic structure!).  Pretty sure this was a Ric Forman wine.  A real treat and EXACTLY what I was hoping for and more. And 13% abv!  Life is good!</p>",
